{
  "texts": [
    "At the corresponding 𝑘-th (𝑘 ≥ 𝑙) layer, we derive contextual semantics from the output tokens w 𝑘+1 using a linear layer Linear(•): c 𝑖 = Linear(w 𝑘+1).",
    "The resulting c 𝑖 aggregates pertinent information to the currently perceived image from the entire context, facilitating the generation of visual tokens aligned with contextual semantics.",
    "Efficient TrainingWe perform both interactions at the final layer of the Q-former and W-former, which means 𝑙 = 𝑘 = 12 (defined in Section 4.2).",
    "We compare the different choices of 𝑙 and 𝑘 in Section 5.3.",
    "For efficient training, we freeze the parameters of the vision encoder and the LLM."
  ]
}